    public class DLPHead
extends DLPElementAdapter
implements net.sf.tweety.logics.commons.syntax.interfaces.AssociativeFormula<DLPLiteral>, net.sf.tweety.logics.commons.syntax.interfaces.Disjunctable, net.sf.tweety.logics.commons.syntax.interfaces.ComplexLogicalFormula, net.sf.tweety.logics.commons.syntax.AssociativeFormulaSupport.AssociativeSupportBridge
    This formula represents the head of an disjunctive rule which is a disjunction of ELP literals. An ELP itself only allows one literal in the head.
    Author:
    Tim Janus
